OL,3,CDad of boy accused of murder tells
OL,4,Ctrial son was 'scared'
OL,6,FHis father told the court the knife
OL,7,Fwas used to "make sharp cuts in
OL,8,Fplants" at their home.
OL,10,FAlfie's mother left court in tears as
OL,11,Fthe prosecutor Craig Hassall KC summed
OL,12,Fup his case, demonstrating how the
OL,13,Fprosecution believe Alfie was stabbed.
OL,15,FMr Hassall said: "Witnesses are all
OL,16,Fconsistent, none of them suggest that
OL,17,FAlfie Lewis was the aggressor."
