OL,3,CDad of boy accused of murder tells
OL,4,Ctrial son was 'scared'
OL,6,FMr Hassall said that the defendant's
OL,7,Fclaim that he was acting in self
OL,8,Fdefence and out of fear of Alfie was
OL,9,Fnot credible.
OL,11,F"The defendant having said nothing to
OL,12,Fanyone about his thoughts or his plans
OL,13,Fwalked up to Alfie brandishing a
OL,14,Fknife. Alfie saw him coming and
OL,15,Fimplored him to 'chill out'.
OL,17,F"What else can anyone intend when they
OL,18,Fplunge a sharp knife into the centre
OL,19,Fof someone's chest," he said.
